d. **.txt amendment target inference** — I use `r"(.+)\.amendment\.\d+\.txt$"` regex. Does this correctly handle edge cases like `weird.name.amendment.9.amendment.1.txt`? (regex is greedy, so it would match target=`weird.name.amendment.9`). That target isn't in REQUIRED_CONTRACT_FILES so the next check would reject, but it's fragile.

e. **`cmd_amend` precondition ordering** — I do:
   1. Load lock
