   3. gate_evidence_sha256/closed_at guards
   4. tamper-evident check
   5. amendment file existence
   6. duplicate guard
   7. target inference + validation
   8. meeting existence
   9. sha compute + write new lock
   10. validate_amendments
   11. on failure: rollback
   12. on success: event append

   Is there a step order issue? Specifically, should I run validate_amendments BEFORE writing the lock, just to simulate? Currently I write-validate-rollback which means disk state flickers.

